<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="364" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,484,1588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1383,1408]" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1869" box="[327,585,1384,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Euschizomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneus">
<emphasis box="[327,585,1384,1408]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Euschizomerus aeneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jithmon &amp; Thomas" authorityYear="2018" box="[743,927,1384,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Euschizomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="devagiriensis">
<emphasis box="[743,927,1384,1408]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">E. devagiriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with broad and apically rounded prosternal process in contrast to the slender and apically pointed prosternal process and medially expanded lateral margin of pronotum which is rounded in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jithmon &amp; Thomas" authorityYear="2018" box="[500,681,1456,1480]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Euschizomerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="devagiriensis">
<emphasis box="[500,681,1456,1480]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">E. devagiriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus box="[685,744,1457,1481]" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Type</typeStatus>
locality of the 
<typeStatus box="[918,1016,1455,1480]" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">holotype</typeStatus>
is labelled as “Deccan” by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="3" pageNumber="364" refId="ref3852" refString="Chaudoir, M. De (1869) Descriptions de Cicindeletes et de Carabiques nouveaux. Revue et Magasin de Zoologie Pure et Appliquee, Series 2, 21, 114 - 122." type="journal article">Chaudoir 1869</bibRefCitation>
. However, its distribution in central Indian region of Deccan plateau is a point of contention, as 
<bibRefCitation pageId="3" pageNumber="364" refId="ref3729" refString="Andrewes, H. E. (1930) Catalogue of Indian Insects. Part 18. Carabidae. Government of India Central Publication Branch, Calcutta, 388 pp." type="book">Andrewes 1930</bibRefCitation>
added the comment, “Deccan” (Probably 
<collectingCountry box="[712,847,1527,1552]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[863,935,1528,1552]" country="Bangladesh" name="Dhaka" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Dacca</collectingRegion>
) indicating that 
<collectingRegion box="[1133,1203,1529,1552]" country="Bangladesh" name="Dhaka" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Dacca</collectingRegion>
was mislabelled as Deccan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
